title: dyn* ICE  primitive read not possible for type: [i32; 4]

labels.name: I-ICE
labels.description: Issue: The compiler panicked, giving an Internal Compilation Error (ICE) ❄️

labels.name: T-compiler
labels.description: Relevant to the compiler team, which will review and decide on the PR/issue.

labels.name: requires-nightly
labels.description: This issue requires a nightly compiler in some way.

body:
### Code ```Rust #![feature(dyn_star)] #![allow(incomplete_features)] use core::fmt::Debug; fn main() { let i = [1, 2, 3, 4] as dyn* Debug; dbg!(i); } ``` ### Meta `rustc --version --verbose`: ``` rustc 1.66.0-nightly (e7119a030 2022-09-22) ``` ### Error output ``` [](error: internal compiler error: /rustc/e7119a0300b87a3d670408ee8e847c6821b3ae80/compiler/rustc_const_eval/src/interpret/operand.rs:390:13: primitive read not possible for type: [i32; 4]) ```
